#payment.hidden
    .ui.container(style="width: 70%;")
        .limit(style="padding: 0;")
            h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
                .content
                    i.book.icon
                    span#narrate-title-payment Request for Untraceable Payment Methods
            .ui.centered.stackable.grid
                .ten.wide.column
                    p 
                        span#narrate-1-payment 
                            span When the caller demands payment 
                        strong#narrate-2-payment  
                            span via cash, gift cards, wire transfers, or even cryptocurrency, 
                        span#narrate-3-payment  
                            span it is a warning sign for a grandparent scam. 
                    p 
                        span#narrate-4-payment  
                            span The scammer may claim these untraceable payment methods allow for faster transfers than checks. 
                        span#narrate-5-payment  
                            span However, this excuse creates a false sense of urgency to pressure you into sending money quickly. 
                        em#narrate-6-payment  
                            span Do not use any untraceable payment methods they suggest.

                    .callout
                        .dark-blue-square
                            img(src=user.avatarImg, alt='avatar picture')
                        .light-blue-content
                            h3.call-header#narrate-7-payment  
                                span Important
                            p#narrate-8-payment  
                                span The real reason scammers demand these methods is that:
                            .ui.bulleted.list
                                .item(style="margin-top: -10px;")#narrate-9-payment  
                                    span The money cannot be reversed or recovered once sent 
                                .item#narrate-10-payment  
                                    span Anonymous payments make it easier for scammers to avoid being traced or caught

                .six.wide.column
                    div.ui.header
                        i.phone.volume.icon
                        | Audio Example
                    .audio-player
                        .wrap
                            audio#audio.with-transcript(controls)
                                source(src="https://dart-store.s3.amazonaws.com/grandparent-audio/untrace.mp3" type="audio/mpeg")
                                | Your browser does not support the audio element.
                            ul#transcript(data-audio-file="https://dart-store.s3.amazonaws.com/grandparent-audio/untrace.mp3" style="max-height: 200px;")
                                li.speaker1.current(data-timecode="00:00") Scammer: I'm at the store, Grandpa. They have the phone I need, but I can't pay for it.
                                li.speaker2(data-timecode="00:05") Grandpa: What do I need to do?
                                li.speaker1(data-timecode="00:06") Scammer: Grandpa, I need you to buy a gift card for me. Can you do it?
                                li.speaker2(data-timecode="00:09") Grandpa: A gift card? Why?
                                li.speaker1(data-timecode="00:12") Scammer: Yes, Grandpa. Buy an iTunes gift card for $500. I'll use it to purchase the phone online.
                                li.speaker2(data-timecode="00:18") Grandpa: Alright, I'll try. How do I do that?
                                li.speaker1(data-timecode="00:21") Scammer: Just go to the store and ask for an iTunes gift card. Once you have it, scratch off the back to reveal the code, and then text me the code. I'll take care of the rest.